{
  "texts": [
    "This enables more in-depth customization for further investigation.",
    "For instance, in Fig. 4b-d, we illustrated the co-occurrence vocabulary of the word '国 (nation)' in keystone works of three philosophical schools.",
    "The divergence in views on righteousness and benefit between Confucianism and Mohism is shown in their co-occurrence frequency: Confucianism places more emphasis on righteousness, while Mohism slightly leans towards benefit.",
    "The highest frequency of the word '人 (person)' implies the individualistic characteristic of Taoism.",
    "This module can be utilized in the study of diverse lexical categories."
  ]
}